
// Checking version of node js installed
node -v

// Running a node js file
node <filename.js>

npm --> node package manager
express --> provides easy and flexible routing system. / contains middleware framework.(the code in the middle of the request and response)
nodemon --> helps to update browser content dynamically. (without running command again and again)

// To install package.json & package-lock.json file
npm init
<fill out the required info and then see your saved inputs in package.json file>

// To install express and adding it to dependencies
npm install express -save

// To uninstall express
npm uninstall express --no-save
< This command does not remove express from dependencies, you have to do it manually >

// To install all the dependencies mentioned in package.json
npm install

// To install nodemon --------------- REMAINING-----------------//
npm install nodemon -g
< Note: nodemon is installed globally, so you won't be able to see nodemon files in your project directory >

Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned

//---------Installing view engine or the template engine----------//
// To install Embedded Javascript i.e ejs
npm install ejs -save
// <% javascript code %>   <%= output code %>

//---------Handling post requests using body parser middleware----------//
// To install body-parser middleware
npm install body-parser -save

//---------node mailer used to send emails from nodejs application----------//

//---------Installing mongoose to deal with mongodb----------//
npm install mongoose -save
